observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

instruct the GSO and Municipal Accountant to reconcile the local road inventory report and road map with the Accounting records;

appraise the road lots components to be recorded as part of the Road Network System.

We recommended that the Management instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
review the composition of these payable accounts to determine valid claims and ensure that all payables are duly supported with the required documents;
revert, if warranted, in the unappropriated surplus of the Municipality those which had become outstanding for two years or more in accordance with Section 98 of PD No. 1445;
prepare the necessary adjusting journal entries to correct the erroneous entries;
observe proper accounting treatment on accounts payable recognition and make the necessary adjustments to fairly present the affected liability, assets and expenses account balances; and
strictly comply with the timely withholding of taxes and effect the adjusting entries to recognize the withholding taxes portion of Accounts Payable.

We recommended that the Management:
Reclassify the small tangible items currently recorded as PPE to Inventory;
Adjust the accounting records and financial statements accordingly to reflect a fair presentation of PPE, related accumulated depreciation and depreciation expenses, and Government Equity accounts;
Ensure that all small tangible items are monitored through Inventory Custodian Slips (ICS) to establish accountability; and
Conduct an orientation or refresher training for Accounting personnel and GSO-Designate on current COA policies regarding asset classification and capitalization thresholds to ensure proper application of updated accounting policies.

We recommended that the Management:
revise the LDRRMFP to reflect the QRF as a lump sum allocation, without itemization, in accordance with Section 6.2.1 of Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-1;
ensure strict compliance with the guidelines on the usage of QRF, limiting its utilization to immediate disaster response and recovery efforts during or after a declared calamity;
conduct orientation or capacity-building sessions for LDRRMO, LDRRM Council, the Local Finance Committee, and other relevant officers/personnel to reinforce understanding of applicable disaster fund policies.

